author: COMSOL
description:
This example models the deposition of an inductor coil in 3D.

The geometry includes the extrusion of the deposition pattern into an isolating photoresist mask, and a diffusion layer on top of the photoresist. The mass transfer of copper ions in the electrolyte has a major impact on the deposition kinetics, resulting in higher deposition rates in the outer parts of the deposition pattern.

The model is solved in a time-dependent study using a deformed geometry.
